  "prompt": "Where can I get COMSOL Multiphysics full version software?",
  "response": "You can obtain the full version of COMSOL Multiphysics software through the following avenues:\n\n1. **Official COMSOL Website**: The most direct way to purchase the software is via the official COMSOL website. They provide options for different licensing models (such as single-user licenses, site licenses, and academic licenses). You can visit [COMSOL's website](https://www.comsol.com) to explore your options.\n\n2. **Authorized Distributors**: COMSOL has a network of authorized distributors around the world. You can find a list of these distributors on the COMSOL website, which may offer region-specific support and purchasing options.\n\n3. **University Licenses**: If you are affiliated with a university, check if your institution has a site license for COMSOL Multiphysics. Many universities provide access to the software for students and faculty.\n\n4. **Free Trial**: If you're interested in trying the software before purchasing, COMSOL offers a free trial version. You can request access through their website.\n\n5. **Educational Discounts**: If you are a student or educator, look for potential discounts or academic licenses that offer the software at a reduced price.\n\nMake sure to check the terms and conditions of the license that applies to your use case.",
